Immunization

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

http://smart.who.int/ig/smart-immunizations/ImplementationGuide/who.fhir.immunization

WHO Immunization Implementation Guide.

resource.name: IMMZ.D2.DT.Polio.Birth
resource.description:
Determine if the client is due for a polio vaccination according to the national immunization protocol.
Birth dose administration as part of "bOPV plus IPV" schedule (In countries that are polio-endemic countries or countries at high risk for importation and subsequent spread of poliovirus, that follow the combined bOPV-IPV schedule)

resource.name: IMMZ.D2.DT.Polio.bOPV.MR
resource.description: Provide immunization

resource.name: IMMZ.D2.DT.Polio.bOPVIPV
resource.description:

bOPV plus IPV schedule (applicable for all countries)

resource.name: IMMZ.D2.DT.Polio.IPV.MR
resource.description: Provide immunization

resource.name: IMMZ.D2.DT.Polio.IPVOnly
resource.description:
Determine if the client is due for a polio vaccination according to the national immunization protocol.
IPV-only (in countries, in polio-free regions, with a very low risk of importation and sustained high routine immunization coverage (DTP3 >90%)

resource.name: IMMZ.D2.DT.Polio.Sequential
resource.description:
Determine if the client is due for a polio vaccination according to the national immunization protocol.
Sequential IPV–bOPV schedule (in countries with high vaccination coverage (e.g. 90–95%) and low importation risk (where neighbouring countries and/or countries that share substantial population movement have a similarly high coverage))
